From 9989e0e7433b8940efb4e2a94ed37eed0c97ad1f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 09:02:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(india): NSE primary, Screener.in fallback for quarterly
 P&L
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The earnings-analysis page footer was labeling sources as
'financials: screener_in · history: screener_in' even though NSE has
the authoritative quarterly filing data. Screener was the only source
because india-screener route only parsed the Screener HTML.

Now NSE corporates-financial-results runs in parallel with Screener and,
when it returns 4+ valid quarterly filings within the last 3 years,
overrides the quarterly/latest/qoq/yoy arrays with NSE-derived values
(Lakhs converted to Cr). Screener.in continues to supply TTM ratios,
annual P&L history, balance sheet, cash flow, shareholding pattern,
and sector classification — fields NSE does not expose.

Outputs:
 - source: 'nse_primary' when NSE supplied the quarterly P&L
 - source: 'screener_in' when only Screener was available
 - new provenance object detailing per-field origin
 - sources.financials / sources.history reflect NSE when used

Also adds a graceful Screener-down path that returns NSE-only payload
(empty TTM ratios) instead of 404'ing.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
